<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Teaching you to interfere with me for over two wonderful years</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twoxenos>TwoXenos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Two Xenos! One LOW price!</span><br>  Posts: 293<br> <font color=#000080>(9/10/03 6:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: LDoN Experiences</span><hr size=1> I did one adventure last night; started in the camp in Butcherblock (Mistmoore theme).  Our task was to kill 60 mobs within a 90 minute time limit.  Group was me, 65 chanter, 65 druid, 65 ranger, 65 bard and 64 necro--pretty balanced, but not outrageous dps.<br>
<br>
The zone in was on the west wall of LFay, towards the south, so it was a bit of a run to get there.  We finished buffing before zoning in, because we didn't want to waste time in the zone buffing up.  Zoned in and started working our way through.<br>
<br>
Cool looking zone; layout was sort-of like Veksar, mostly linear with a few dead ends.  Almost all mobs were undead; I think the mobs were around level 55ish, but didn't get much chance to check.  Fair number of casters, and a few named in the mix.  Mobs were packed pretty tight, and there was no time to really work on getting singles, so it was pretty much 2-4 mobs at a time the whole way.  Bard was useful a few times to disarm traps.<br>
<br>
We had a couple of deaths along the way, largely from people breaking mezz (tho I was sometimes targeting people for heals, so /assist wasn't 100% effective).  A few decent items dropped, including some nice leather legs, similar to Elysian the druid said, but dru/monk/bst and either rec or req level 60.  Cash loot was pretty good.<br>
<br>
We started sorta slow but then hit our stride and ended up killing the 60th mob with around 20 minutes left on the timer.  We got a message that we had succeeded and that we had 30 minutes to leave the zone.  We continued killing mobs in the zone till the 30 minutes was up, at which point we were booted to LFay.  Reward was 51 adventure points for most people, the necro got 49 ('cause of level perhaps?).   Ranger said there were about 10-15 mobs left in the zone when we were done; dunno if there is a bonus for clearing the zone within the time limit.<br>
<br>
We did the normal version of the adventure; I'd be curious to see if the hard version means higher level mobs or a higher required kill count.  I'd think the latter would be more likely, but there's only one way to find out.  =)<br>
<br>
P.S.  I'm going to be /petition'ing and /feedback'ing on how much I dislike the leaderboard until they either kill it or let us opt out of it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=445044" target="top">Xenophon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 65 Paladin<br>
